# ==============================================================================
# era — Mobile (Expo) Environment Contract
# ==============================================================================
#
# READ THIS BEFORE ADDING ANY VARIABLE.
#
# An Expo app bundle ships to the user's physical device. EVERY value present
# in the mobile environment at build time is INLINED into the JavaScript bundle
# and is trivially extractable by anyone who downloads the app (unzip the .ipa /
# .apk, or read it at runtime). There is no such thing as a "secret" in a mobile
# client bundle.
#
# THEREFORE, THIS FILE INTENTIONALLY CONTAINS ONLY `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` VARIABLES.
# Anything prefixed EXPO_PUBLIC_ is PUBLIC by definition — treat every value here
# as if it were printed on a billboard.
#
# NEVER add server secrets to this file or to the mobile environment, including:
#   - DATABASE_URL / any DB connection string
#   - auth / session / JWT signing secrets
#   - R2 / S3 / object-storage access keys or secret keys
#   - AI provider API keys (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
#   - any other private credential
#
# The ABSENCE of server secrets below is DELIBERATE, not an omission. Those
# secrets live only in the API server runtime (apps/web server). The mobile app
# performs any secret-bearing operation by making an AUTHENTICATED CALL to that
# API — it never holds the secret itself.
#
# ==============================================================================

# Base URL of the era API server the app authenticates against and calls.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.era.example.com

# Public CDN base URL for wardrobe asset images (public bucket, no credentials).
EXPO_PUBLIC_R2_PUBLIC_URL=https://assets.era.example.com
